import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='net_generation', data=data, color='blue')
    chart.axhline(y=data['net_generation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.pivot(index='year', columns='source', values='net_generation')
    ax = sns.barplot(data=data, x=data.index, y='renewables', color='green', label='Renewables')
    ax = sns.barplot(data=data, x=data.index, y='natural gas', color='blue', label='Natural Gas', bottom=data['renewables'])
    ax = sns.barplot(data=data, x=data.index, y='coal', color='red', label='Coal', bottom=data['natural gas']+data['renewables'])
    ax.set_ylabel('Net Generation (MWh)')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_title('What is the contribution of each energy source to the net generation of electricity in Iowa?')
    ax.legend(loc='upper left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='net_generation', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['net_generation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean = {:.2f}'.format(data['net_generation'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(data['net_generation'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median = {:.2f}'.format(data['net_generation'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of net generation of electricity in Iowa?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Net Generation (MWh)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='net_generation', hue='source', data=data, palette='colorblind')
    plt.title('What is the trend in net generation of electricity for each energy source in Iowa?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Net Generation (MWh)')
    plt.legend(title='Energy Source', loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
